    "summary": "As an entrepreneur, executive leader, and board member, I have extensive experience increasing profitability and driving sustainable growth for early state medical device and biotechnology companies. \n\nI am highly innovative and proactive with earned recognition for building numerous strategic partnerships, guiding the development of next-generation technology, quickly bringing innovative products to markets, and capturing #1 market positioning in the U.S. and abroad.\n\nThroughout my career, I have earned recognition for taking four companies public and co-founding two world leading medical device companies while capturing lucrative fundraising opportunities ($200M+), driving international growth, and executing multi-million-dollar through $2B company sales.\n\nENTREPRENEURSHIP HIGHLIGHTS:\n\n\u2713 Arthrocare Corporation - Created this organization as a result of developing a wildly successful product for arthroscopists at Citation Medical, which quickly earned recognition and was adopted as the gold standard product. Executed successful IP by Robbie Stevens and ultimate $2B acquisition.\n\n\u2713 Medlink Europe - Established an organization to help U.S. early stage medical device and life science companies enter the European marketplace. Executed $10M company sale.\n\n\u2713 Endovia - Partnered with Dr. David Brock (Chief of Artificial Intelligence at MIT) to develop a robotic system for use in general surgery as well as a robotic catheter for intra cardiac and intra vascular procedures. Captured an exclusive patent enabling working access through the aortic valve.\n\n\u2713 Haemonetics Corporation - Envisioned, launched, scaled, and sold a company that developed centrifugal based blood separating and processing systems with proprietary capital equipment and disposable centrifugal chambers and tubing sets. Grew company from <$8M to $60M+, captured #1 market positioning, and led successful IPO on NYSE.\n\nBOARD LEADERSHIP & ADVISOR TO CEO:\n\n\u2713 Selected as Executive Advisor and Board Member to steer multiple organizations towards a sustainable future. Guide business strategy, fundraising, relationship building, market growth, and global adoption strategies.\n\n\u2713 Serve and/or served as Board Member for Circulogene Theranosics, Arthrocare Corporation, Medlink Europe, Endovia, Tonometrics, Shaw Medical, Citation Medical, and Haemonetics Corporation.\n\nAREAS OF EXPERTISE:\n\nStrategic Planning | Sales & Business Development | Digital Marketing | People Management | Revenue & Profit Growth | Client Relationship Development | P&L | Fundraising | Product Development & Launch | Technology Innovation",
